The paper deals with the problem of annotation quality in neural networks, specifically in the task of computed tomography (CT) imaging segmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed clearing algorithm involves assigning confidence levels to annotators and nodules, which involves machine learning techniques and could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the possibility of applying the algorithm to other tasks such as semantic segmentation, classification, and regression, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
